Global Inactivated Porcine Atrophic Rhinitis Vaccine Market Insights
Inactivated Porcine Atrophic Rhinitis Vaccine Market size was valued at USD 0.25 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 0.35 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 4.0% from 2024 to 2030.

Inactivated Porcine Atrophic Rhinitis Vaccine Market Overview
The Inactivated Porcine Atrophic Rhinitis (PAR) Vaccine market has witnessed significant growth due to increasing concerns about livestock health, particularly in pigs. The global market for these vaccines is valued at approximately USD 650 million in 2025, with a steady growth rate over the forecast period. This market is driven by the rising demand for efficient vaccines to control atrophic rhinitis, a respiratory disease affecting swine populations. The growing industrialization of animal farming and the increasing awareness of animal welfare contribute to the market's expansion. A rise in demand for pork and other pig-derived products globally is expected to fuel this growth further.

